  "implemented_capabilities": [
    "Run state shape validation fails closed when required recovery evidence is missing.",
    "Resume decisions resolve to SKIP, REPLAY, BLOCK_HUMAN_GATE, BLOCK_INVALIDATION, BLOCK_LOCK_BOUNDARY, or BLOCK_UNSAFE_STATE.",
    "Invalidation records use stable reason codes with affected node, path, prior value, current value, stop rule, and Human Gate flag.",
    "Review recovery recomputes candidate subject hashes and detects missing, stale, invalid, hash-changed, or non-approved review decisions without writing approvals.",
    "Lock rebuild behavior produces sorted request packets and dry-run evidence only; it never creates, rewrites, deletes, or publishes locks.",
    "Program driver resume hook delegates to recovery when a declared run state file exists while preserving safe stop behavior for missing state refs.",
    "Upstream lock hash drift routes to Human Gate rather than ordinary replay invalidation.",
    "Lock rebuild request packets require an existing source lock so source_lock_sha256 is a real file hash, not a sentinel value.",
    "Program driver default upstream P3 build lock binding resolves from the start package root while preserving the canonical relative DAG read ref."
  ],
